ation Oshigambo Secondary School, Namibia (1965)<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td valign=\"top\"><strong>Career<\/strong><\/td>\n<td valign=\"top\">Teacher of Science and Mathematics Harlem Preparatory School \u2013 New York City, USA 1975 \u2013 1978; Head of Science Department Namibia Education Centre, Kwanza Sul, Angola 1979 \u2013 1980; School Principal Namibia Education Centre, Deputy Director and Deputy Commander of the Namibia Health and Education Centre, Kwanza Sul, Angola 1980 \u2013 1985; SWAPO Deputy Secretary for Education and Culture 1985 \u2013 1987; Personal Secretary of the SWAPO President, Luanda Angola 1987 \u2013 1988; Assistant Director and Head of Department of Education and Teacher Training, United Nations Institute for Namibia, Lusaka \u2013 Zambia 1988 \u2013 1998; Adviser on Administrative Matters to the SWAPO Director of Elections 1989; Secretary to Cabinet 1990 \u2013 1993; Chief Executive Officer of Joint Administrative Authority for Walvis Bay and Off-Shore Islands 1992 \u2013 1993<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Interests<\/strong><\/td>\n<td valign=\"top\">Research on Namibian History; Co-author of \u201cNamibia in History\u201d; Co-author of \u201cUnderstanding History\u201d book series for Namibia Junior Secondary Schools; Co-editor of \u201cThrough the Flames\u201d; Poems from the Namibian Liberation struggle<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Vice President SWAPO Party Legislative Profile Member of the SWAPO Political Bureau\u00a01998 \u2013 Present; Member of the SWAPO Central Committee\u00a01995 \u2013 Present; Secretary General\u00a02013 \u2013 Present; Minister of Safety and Security\u00a02010 &#8211; 2012; Minister of Education\u00a02005 \u2013 2010; Minister of Information and Broadcasting\u00a02008 \u2013 2005; Minister of Finance\u00a01996 \u2013 2003; Minister of Agriculture, Water and&hellip;<\/p>\n","protected":false},"featured_media":4638,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":